screen_data.content:
OVERVIEW:
The 'vars' section defines screen variables that hold data.
Each variable can have a display component for user interaction.

BASIC STRUCTURE:
<pre>
  screen myScreen = {
      "vars": [
          {
              "name": "username",
              "type": "string",
              "default": ""
          },
          {
              "name": "age",
              "type": "int",
              "default": 0
          }
      ]
  };
</pre>

VARIABLE PROPERTIES:
• name - Variable identifier (required)
• type - Data type (string, int, float, double, bool, json, array, etc.)
• default - Initial value
• display - Display component configuration (optional)

SUPPORTED DATA TYPES:
• Primitives: string, int, long, float, double, byte, bool
• Collections: array, json, map
• Complex: record, bitmap, intmap
• Special: date, canvas

ACCESSING DATA:
<pre>
  // Direct property access
  myScreen.username = "Alice";
  print myScreen.username;
</pre>

<pre>
  // Using builtin functions
  call scr.setValue("myScreen", "username", "Bob");
  var name = call scr.getValue("myScreen", "username");
</pre>

EXAMPLE WITH COMPLEX TYPE:
<pre>
  screen dataScreen = {
      "vars": [
          {
              "name": "config",
              "type": "json",
              "default": {"theme": "dark", "size": 14}
          },
          {
              "name": "items",
              "type": "array",
              "default": []
          }
      ]
  };
</pre>

screen_items.content:
OVERVIEW:
Items bind screen variables to display components within areas.
Each item references a variable and is positioned in an area.

BASIC STRUCTURE:
<pre>
  "items": [
      {
          "name": "usernameField",
          "varRef": "username",
          "seq": 1,
          "row": 0,
          "col": 0
      }
  ]
</pre>

ITEM PROPERTIES:

IDENTIFICATION:
• name - Item identifier (required)
• varRef - Variable name to bind (required)
• seq - Sequence number for ordering

POSITIONING (varies by area type):
• row, col - Grid position (gridpane)
• rowSpan, colSpan - Grid cell spanning
• alignment - Item alignment within cell
• relativePos - Relative position (top, bottom, left, right)

SIZING:
• minWidth, prefWidth, maxWidth - Width constraints
• minHeight, prefHeight, maxHeight - Height constraints
• hgrow - Horizontal grow priority
• vgrow - Vertical grow priority

STYLING:
• style - CSS style string
• styleClass - CSS class names

BEHAVIOR:
• editable - Enable/disable editing
• visible - Show/hide item
• disabled - Disable item
• stateful - Track state changes
• mandatory - Required field indicator

EXAMPLE - SIMPLE ITEMS:
<pre>
  "area": [{
      "name": "formArea",
      "type": "vbox",
      "items": [
          {
              "name": "nameField",
              "varRef": "username",
              "seq": 1
          },
          {
              "name": "emailField",
              "varRef": "email",
              "seq": 2,
              "editable": true
          },
          {
              "name": "saveBtn",
              "varRef": "saveButton",
              "seq": 3
          }
      ]
  }]
</pre>

EXAMPLE - GRID ITEMS:
<pre>
  "area": [{
      "name": "gridArea",
      "type": "gridpane",
      "items": [
          {
              "name": "firstNameField",
              "varRef": "firstName",
              "row": 0,
              "col": 1,
              "hgrow": "ALWAYS"
          },
          {
              "name": "lastNameField",
              "varRef": "lastName",
              "row": 1,
              "col": 1,
              "colSpan": 2,
              "hgrow": "ALWAYS"
          }
      ]
  }]
</pre>

EXAMPLE - STYLED ITEMS:
<pre>
  "items": [{
      "name": "titleField",
      "varRef": "title",
      "style": "-fx-font-size: 18px; -fx-font-weight: bold;",
      "styleClass": "header-field",
      "minWidth": "200",
      "prefWidth": "400"
  }]
</pre>

ITEM OPERATIONS:
<pre>
  // Set item property
  call scr.setProperty("myScreen.emailField", "editable", false);
  call scr.setProperty("myScreen.emailField", "visible", true);
  call scr.setProperty("myScreen.emailField", "tooltip", "Enter email");
</pre>

<pre>
  // Get item property
  var editable = call scr.getProperty("myScreen.emailField", "editable");
  var status = call scr.getItemStatus("myScreen", "emailField");
</pre>

<pre>
  // Item data source
  call scr.setItemSource("myScreen", "emailField", "display");
  var source = call scr.getItemSource("myScreen", "emailField");
</pre>

<pre>
  // Reset item
  call scr.resetItemOriginalValue("myScreen", "emailField");
</pre>

<pre>
  // Get all items
  var itemList = call scr.getItemList("myScreen");
  foreach item in itemList {
      print "Item: " + item;
  }
</pre>

ITEM WITHOUT DISPLAY:
Items can reference variables that have no display component:
<pre>
  "vars": [{"name": "hiddenData", "type": "string"}]
  "items": [{"name": "hidden", "varRef": "hiddenData"}]
</pre>

CHOICE OPTIONS:
For combobox, choicebox, listview - set options dynamically:
<pre>
  var options = ["Option 1", "Option 2", "Option 3"];
  call scr.setItemChoiceOptions("myScreen", "myCombo", options);
  var current = call scr.getItemChoiceOptions("myScreen", "myCombo");
</pre>

ITEM VALIDATION:
<pre>
  // Check if screen has changes
  var changed = call scr.checkChanged("myScreen");
</pre>

<pre>
  // Check for errors
  var hasError = call scr.checkError("myScreen");
</pre>

<pre>
  // Set/get screen status
  call scr.setStatus("myScreen", "changed");
  var status = call scr.getStatus("myScreen");
</pre>

<pre>
  // Set/get error message
  call scr.setError("myScreen", "Validation failed");
  var error = call scr.getError("myScreen");
</pre>

